Big profit-taking in #Dow and #DAX30 amongst retail traders, they were heavy short 71% in the Dow, drops 18% to a slight short 53% on short profit-taking and some range-trading longs entering. DAX retail bias down 19% from heavy short 76% to 57%. #Nasdaq bias little changed.

Rough day for markets with the S&P 500 down 1.8% and the #Dow down 1.9%. Hard to hang this on one bit of news, but it seems global growth concerns are pervasive. The 10-year yield fell below 1.60% for the first time in three weeks.
